{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Clarify criteria for holding a border poll as per the Good Friday Agreement 1998",
        "additional_details": "To date the UK Government has failed to outline detailed criteria that they will use to decide when to hold a Border Poll. It is incumbent on UK Government to publish a criteria and to ensure that they fulfil their commitments in the Good Friday Agreement as co-signatories of this international agreement.",
        "background": "The UK Government must clarify the criteria they will use to decide to hold a Border Poll as per their commitments in the Good Friday Agreement, an agreement overwhelmingly endorsed in democratic referendums by the people of Ireland, north and south.",
